0a%20break-up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lack%20of%20trust%20can%20manifest%20in%20controlling%20and%20paranoid%20behavior%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20asking%20your%20partner%20to%20see%20their%20phone%2C%20or%20to%20check%20their%20messages%20or%20social-media%20accounts%20is%20a%20controlling%20habit%20that%20will%20eventually%20lead%20to%20your%20partner%20being%20defensive%2C%20as%20you%20are%20invading%20their%20privacy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlair%20said%20that%20the%20main%20things%20that%20make%20a%20relationship%20last%20are%20communication%20and%20trust%2C%20and%20if%20you're%20checking%20your%20partner's%20devices%20or%20asking%20other%20people%20about%20them%20in%20an%20obsessive%20way%2C%20that's%20a%20bad%20sign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20people%20who%20don't%20trust%20also%20don't%20have%20confidence%20so%20you%20have%20to%20check%20your%20self-confidence%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20know%20you're%20good%20and%20worthwhile%20it's%20easier%20to%20trust%20that%20someone%20will%20think%20so%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E13.%20You%20push%20people%20away.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224795%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22unhappy%20couple%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ef2aa196b7920019ca4de4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223596%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffear-of-intimacy-2017-9%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epush%20away%20the%20people%20they%20love%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20they%20can%20do%20this%20because%20of%20a%20bad%20relationship%2C%20or%20trauma%20in%20their%20childhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrud%C3%B6%20said%20this%20can%20manifest%20as%20a%20fear%20of%20commitment%2C%20as%20for%20many%20this%20is%20a%20response%20to%20the%20possibility%20of%20being%20hurt%20again.%20Essentially%2C%20you%20might%20be%20scared%20of%20being%20abandoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20might%20find%20that%20you%20are%20subconsciously%20pushing%20your%20new%20partner%20to%20leave%20you%2C%20or%20demand%20constant%20reassurance%20from%20them%2C%20which%20can%20become%20draining%20and%20exhausting%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConstantly%20pushing%20people%20away%20could%20also%20be%20a%20sign%20you%20have%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-avoidant-attachment-style-2018-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eavoidant%20attachment%20style%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20when%20you%20enter%20relationships%20that%20will%20inevitably%20fail%2C%20or%20push%20away%20anyone%20who%20is%20right%20for%20you.%20This%20way%2C%20you%20never%20let%20anybody%20hurt%20you%2C%20but%20you%20don't%20find%20happiness%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESo%20what%20can%20you%20do%3F%20First%2C%20take%20some%20time%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221885%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20and%20a%20woman%20walk%20side-by-side%20through%20a%20park%20in%20Toledo%20Ohio.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ef2ae8bdd7e70019dfcef9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20couple%20walks%20through%20a%20park%20in%20Toledo%20Ohio.%3Cp%3EStephanie%20Noritz%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20sometimes%20find%20themselves%20jumping%20from%20relationship%20to%20relationship%2C%20without%20really%20looking%20inside%20themselves%20to%20see%20where%20some%20of%20their%20deeper%20issues%20lie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20don't%20take%20the%20time%20to%20reflect%2C%20you%20might%20be%20going%20straight%20into%20another%20relationship%20simply%20because%20you%20miss%20the%20intimacy%20and%20closeness%20of%20a%20partner%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20new%20person%20might%