en%20Dardon%2C%20a%20union%20organizer%20and%20a%20patient%20access%20representative%20for%20a%20Kaiser%20Permanente%20hospital%20in%20Oregon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20would%20be%20very%20detrimental%20for%20our%20patients%2C%26quot%3B%20Dardon%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHospitals%20would%20not%20be%20the%20only%20facilities%20impacted.%20The%20Coalition%20also%20represents%20pharmacists%2C%20pharmacy%20techs%2C%20social%20workers%2C%20financial%20services%20providers%2C%20and%20several%20others%20who%20provide%20follow-up%20care%20to%20patients%20outside%20of%20hospitals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20Kaiser%20Permanente's%20responsibility%20to%20prevent%20this%20interruption%2C%20Dardon%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can't%20afford%20to%20have%20workers%20out%20on%20the%20picket%20line%20for%20two%20weeks%20and%20neglect%20patient%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20Dardon%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20part%20falls%20on%20Kaiser.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20about%20interruptions%20to%20patient%20care%2C%20a%20Kaiser%20Permanente%20spokesperson%20directed%20Insider%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.kaiserpermanente.org%2Fwho-we-are%2Flabor-relations%2Falliance-bargaining-updates%2Faddressing-the-coalitions-threat-to-strike%5C%22%3EAugust%2024%20statement.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20take%20any%20threat%20to%20disrupt%20care%20for%20our%20members%20seriously%20and%20have%20plans%20to%20ensure%20continued%20access%20to%20healthcare%20by%20our%20members%2C%20patients%2C%20and%20the%20communities%20we%20serve%2C%20should%20any%20union%20call%20for%20a%20strike%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20reads.%20%26quot%3BOur%20members%2C%20patients%2C%20and%20our%20communities%20need%20us%20to%20be%20there%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20is%20%26quot%3Bconfident%26quot%3B%20they%20will%20reach%20an%20agreement%20with%20workers%20ahead%20of%20their%20contract%20expiration%20on%20September%2030%2C%20accordin