%20Insider.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20settling%20in%20the%20hip%20Shibuya%20and%20Sangenjaya%20districts%20of%20west%20Tokyo%2C%20Wormann%20told%20Insider%20he%20began%20buying%20cheap%2C%20neglected%20properties%20in%20the%20area%20and%20flipping%20them%20to%20rent%20for%20extra%20income.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20learned%20the%20necessary%20DIY%20skills%20watching%20his%20father%20flip%20properties%20in%20Sweden%2C%20Wormann%20said.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuying%20the%20Sangenjaya%20House%20in%20March%202022%20was%20his%20most%20ambitious%20project%20to%20date.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20almost%20100%20years%20old%20and%20had%20been%20empty%20for%20more%20than%2010%20years%20when%20I%20first%20saw%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20previous%20owner%20had%20passed%20away%20in%202010%20so%20it%20was%20owned%20by%20four%20siblings%20who%20just%20did%20not%20know%20what%20to%20do%20with%20it.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWormann%20told%20Insider%20he%20was%20passing%20by%20the%20house%20and%20saw%20the%20owners%20at%20the%20site.%20He%20asked%20if%20they%20were%20interested%20in%20selling.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20owners%20were%20shocked%20that%20Wormann%20wanted%20to%20buy%20the%20house%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Abandoned%20house%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f1ec9557bff700194859e2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EAnton%20Wormann%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B'Really%3F%20You%20want%20to%20buy%20this%20piece%20of%20crap%3F'%20That%20was%20their%20reaction%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20But%20Wormann%20was%20already%20familiar%20with%20the%20process%20of%20flipping%20houses%20in%20Tokyo%20and%20felt%20ready%20for%20the%20challenge.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Wormann%20didn't%20share%20how%20much%20he%20paid%20for%20the%20property%2C%20akiya%20can%20cost%20between%20%2410%2C000%20and%20%24100%2C000%2C%20depending%20on%20their%20condition%20and%20location%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.koryoya.com%2Fabout%2Findex.html%23company%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20akiya%20listing%20site.%3C%2Fa%3E%20A%20more%20modern%20akiya%20in%20Tokyo%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FCvkh046MRfH%2F%3Fimg_index%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elisted%20for%20%2434%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20Instagram%20Cheap%20House%20Japan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWormann%20was%20able%20to%20complete%20the%20purchase%20in%20March%202022.%20He%20told%20Insider%20he%20always%20planned%20to%20rent%20the%20place%20out%2C%20so%20he%20wanted%20to%20incorporate%20Scandinavian%20and%20Japanese%20designs%20that%20would%20appeal%20to%20Airbnb%20guests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20century-old%20house%20is%2090%20square%20meters%20over%20two%20floors.%20It%20originally%20had%20five%20small%20bedrooms%20and%20a%20small%20garden%20in%20the%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Abandoned%20house%20in%20Japan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f1f58257bff70019486624%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20stairway%20Wormann%20replaced%20himself%20in%20the%20living%20area.%3Cp%3EAnton%20Wormann%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWormann%20demolished%20all%20the%20internal%20walls%20on%20the%20ground%20floor.%20He%20installed%20a%20new%20staircase%20and%20combined%20some%20of%20the%20upstairs%20rooms%20to%20make%20them%20more%20spacious.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUpstairs%2C%20he%20retained%20the%20traditional%20Japanese%20accents%2C%20including%20tatami%20mats%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20sliding%20panels%20called%20fusuma%2C%20and%20wood-and-paper%20doors%20called%20shoji.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20ground%20floor%2C%20Wormann%20outfitted%20the%20kitchen%20with%20modern%20appliances.%20He%20also%20installed%20a%20rotenburo%2C%20or%20outdoor%20bath%2C%20in%20the%20back%20garden.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWormann%20wanted%20a%20challenge%2C%20but%20the%20renovation%20wasn't%20easy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWormann%20documented%20many%20of%20his%20struggles%20on%20his%20YouTube%20channel%2C%20%26quot%3BAnton%20in%20Japan.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20love%20a%20good%20challenge%2C%20but%20if%20I%20am%20honest%2C%20I%20had%20no%20idea%20how%20big%20a%20project%20I%20was%20taking%20on%20when%20I%20took%20a%20peek%20inside%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20speak%20Japanese%20fairly%20well%2C%20but%20the%20terminology%20used%20in%20the%20construction%20world%20is%20pretty%20different%20from%20the%20fashion%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20renovation%2C%20he%20handled%20a%20termite%20infestation%20in%20the%20beams%2C%20mountains%20of%20trash%20as%20the%20property%20was%20gutted%2C%20and%20contractors%20who%20could%20be%20unreliable.%20Replacing%20the%20beams%20was%20an%20unforeseen%20cost%20%E2%80%94%20and%20all%20the%20problems%20delayed%20the%20project.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Abandoned%20house%20in%20Japan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f1f57857bff70019486610%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWormann%20took%20down%20the%20walls%20in%20the%20ground%20floor%20of%20the%20house.%3Cp%3EAnton%20Wormann%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%C2%A0Firing%20tradesmen%20isn't%20usually%20done%20in%20Japan%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWormann%20hired%20a%20plumber%20and%20a%20carpenter%20but%20then%20fired%20them%20when%20the%20work%20was%20taking%20too%20long%20and%20not%20up%20to%20the%20standards%20that%20he%20expected.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20not%20something%20that's%20typically%20done%20in%20Japan%2C%20as%20locals%20do%20not%20question%20the%20%26quot%3Bmaster%26quot%3B%20they%20employ%20to%20complete%20a%20task%2C%20but%20Wormann%20said%20he%20was%20on%20a%20budget%20and%20a%20deadline.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20learned%20by%20experience%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWith%20a%20DIY%20renovation%2C%20you%20have%20to%20make%20hundreds%2C%20if%20not%20thousands%2C%20of%20quick%20decisions%20so%20as%20not%20to%20fall%20behind%20schedule%20or%20go%20broke.%20The%20hardest%20things%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20you%20have%20no%20control%20over%2C%20such%20as%20how%20can%20I%20get%20hold%20of%20a%20water%20boiler%2C%20or%20when%20the%20plumber%20says%20he%20cannot%20come%20for%20a%20month.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20plus%20side%2C%20Wormann%20said%20the%20city%20government%20was%20helpful%20with%20the%20paperwork.%20He%20told%20Insider%20local%20governments%20across%20Japan%20are%20very%20keen%20to%20solve%20the%20problem%20of%20abandoned%20and%20collapsing%20akiya.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Abandoned%20house%20in%20Japan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f1f5805114270019af240c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20old%20owners%20left%20piles%20of%20trash%20and%20old%20belongings%20Wormann%20had%20to%20clean%20up.%3Cp%3EAnton%20Wormann%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPersonal%20contacts%20in%20the%20real-estate%20business%20and%20among%20local%20tradesmen%20helped%20Wormann%20finish%20on%20time%20and%20on%20budget.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20estimates%20that%20he%20put%20in%20about%201%2C500%20hours%20of%20his%20own%20labor%20on%20the%20house%20and%20spent%20some%20%2450%2C000%20on%20materials%20and%20laborers.%20The%20rebuild%20took%20a%20year%20to%20complete%2C%20with%20Wormann%20working%20on-site%20when%20he%20wasn't%20traveling%20for%20modeling%20jobs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Sangenjaya%20house%20was%20completed%20in%20March%2C%20and%20Wormann%20told%20Insider%20he%20had%20his%20first%20Airbnb%20guests%20within%20a%20month.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20still%20live%20in%20the%20area%20and%20whenever%20it%20is%20not%20rented%20out%2C%20I%20have%20friends%20over%20for%20dinner%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20hope%20my%20mum%20can%20come%20and%20visit%20next%20year%20during%20the%20cherry-blossom%20season.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOthers%20looking%20to%20buy%20an%20akiya%20should%20do%20their%20research%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWormann%20already%20has%20his%20eyes%20on%20his%20next%20akiya%20renovation%20and%20has%20written%20a%20book%20that%20will%20be%20available%20in%20October%20with%20advice%20for%20anyone%20thinking%20of%20taking%20on%20a%20similar%20project.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bottom%20line%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20not%20to%20buy%20the%20first%20property%20you%20see%2C%20stay%20calm%2C%20and%20choose%20the%20area%20where%20you%20want%20to%20live.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJapan%20has%2010%20million%20vacant%20houses%20and%20this%20market%20is%20growing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20if%20you%20contribute%20to%20a%20community%20then%20opportunities%20will%20arise%20around%20you.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-japan-abandoned-home-flipped-airbnb-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693819754000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f5a2ed781926001910d168%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-japan-abandoned-home-flipped-airbnb-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%2030-year-old%20Swedish%20model%20moved%20to%20Tokyo%20and%20started%20buying%20and%20renovating%20%26quot%3Bakiya%26quo