tu%20in%20Chicago%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ed234715cc5d00198ca4c5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221066%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVinod%20Kalathil%20and%20his%20wife%20Margaret%20Pak%20recently%20opened%20no-tip%20restaurant%20Thattu%20in%20Chicago.%3Cp%3EVinod%20Kalathil%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EVinod%20Kalathil%20and%20his%20wife%20recently%20opened%20the%20restaurant%20Thattu%20in%20Chicago.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20restaurant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpeople-tip-less-often-tipping-culture-2023-6%5C%22%3Edoesn't%20take%20tips%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20instead%20pays%20servers%20a%20competitive%20wage.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThey%20adopted%20the%20policy%20after%20noticing%20that%20some%20customers%20dislike%20tipping%20on%20credit%20card%20readers.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20an%20as-told-to%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Vinod%20Kalathil%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20Thattu%2C%20a%20no-tip%20restaurant%20in%20Chicago.%20This%20conversation%20has%20been%20condensed%20and%20edited%20for%20clarity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20wife%20and%20I%20opened%20our%20restaurant%2C%20Thattu%2C%20about%20four%20months%20ago%20on%20the%20Northwest%20side%20of%20Chicago.%20We%20serve%20food%20from%20Kerala%2C%20a%20state%20in%20southern%20India%20where%20I'm%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20don't%20charge%20our%20customers%20a%20service%20fee%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-to-tip-uber-hairstylist-housekeeping-delivery-2018-5%5C%22%3Eexpect%20them%20to%20leave%20tips%3C%2Fa%3E.%20So%2C%20our%20prices%20are%20about%2015%20to%2020%25%20higher%20than%20they'd%20be%20if%20we%20were%20adding%20those%20charges%20onto%20the%20bill.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20we%20opened%2C%20we%20talked%20to%20other%20restaurant%20owners%20about%20plans%20for%20opening%20a%20%26quot%3Bno-tip%26quot%3B%20restaurant.%20The%20standard%20response%20we%20got%20from%20all%20of%20them%20was%20that%20it%20wouldn't%20work.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusinesses-ask-for-tips-pay-workers-less-recession-fears-2023-7%5C%22%3ECustomers%20would%20balk%20at%20our%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20said.%20I%20say%20the%20prices%20reflect%20the%20true%20cost%20of%20dining%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20part%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20dining%20at%20Thattu%20goes%20to%20helping%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fservice-workers-resignations-bring-up-wages-end-tipping-nyt-2021-9%5C%22%3Ewait%20staff%20earn%20a%20consistent%20and%20competitive%20wage%3C%2Fa%3E.%20We%20pay%20them%20about%20%2419%20an%20hour.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20we%20distribute%20about%208%25%20of%20all%20our%20sales%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20they're%20from%20the%20restaurant%2C%20the%20bar%2C%20any%20catering%20we%20do%2C%20or%20our%20small%20retail%20section%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20between%20all%20of%20our%20employees.%20So%20our%20waiters%20take%20home%20between%20%2424%20or%20%2425%20an%20hour%20on%20average.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELabor%20makes%20up%20more%20than%20half%20of%20our%20total%20costs%20and%20that's%20how%20we%20planned%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20actually%20opened%20the%20first%20iteration%20of%20Thattu%20back%20in%202019%20in%20a%20food%20hall%20in%20Politan%20Row.%20It%20was%20a%20busy%20time.%20My%20wife%20and%20I%20were%20working%20close%20to%2014%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20seven%20days%20a%20week%2C%20until%20the%20pandemic%20hit%2010%20months%20later%2C%20and%20we%20had%20to%20close.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20we%20began%20doing%20pop-ups%20every%20month%20or%20so%20for%20the%20next%20two%20years.%20With%20some%20pop-ups%2C%20customers%20would%20pay%20for%20the%20order%20online%2C%20and%20come%20pick%20it%20up%20from%20us.%20During%20other%20pop-ups%2C%20customers%20would%20pay%20using%20a%20card%20reader%20from%20Square.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20readers%20have%20suggested%20tip%20amounts.%20We%20noticed%20that%20when%20a%20server%20was%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20a%20customer%20with%20a%20handheld%20device%2C%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcustomers-being-asked-to-tip-everywhere-theyre-sick-of-it-2023-3%5C%22%3Eseemed%20to%20feel%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure%20to%20tip%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20a%20little%20confrontational%20to%20put%20something%20in%20front%20of%20them%20%E2%80%93%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20friction%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20another%20reason%20we%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouth-park-creators-eliminate-tips-casa-bonita-pay-30-hour-2023-6%5C%22%3Edecided%20to%20eliminate%20tips%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20because%20we%20wanted%20to%20avoid%20these%20interactions%20with%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Thattu%20outing%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f20ca257bff70019489596%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20staff%20of%20Thattu%20took%20a%20group%20outing%20funded%20by%20the%20cash%20tips%20they%20received.%3Cp%3EVinod%20Kalathil%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Thattu%2C%20some%20people%20still%20insist%20on%20leaving%20tips.%20They'll%20come%20to%20the%20bar%2C%20hand%20us%20cash%2C%20and%20say%20%26quot%3BHey%20you%20guys%20did%20a%20really%20great%20job.%26quot%3B%20So%20tips%20are%20really%20an%20expression%20of%20customer%20goodwill%20rather%20than%20income%20our%20wait%20staff%20is%20relying%20on.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20asked%20our%20employees%20what%20they%20wanted%20to%20do%20with%20these%20cash%20tips.%20We%20decided%20that%20we%20would%20use%20it%20to%20buy%20coffee%2C%20and%20pop%2C%20and%20beer%20for%20the%20employees.%20Sometimes%20we%20use%20it%20to%20buy%20ice%20cream%20for%20everyone.%20A%20couple%20of%20weeks%20ago%20we%20even%20had%20a%20group%20outing.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20city%20of%20Chicago%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fminimum-wage-tipping-restaurant-workers-shortage-2022-1%5C%22%3Erethinking%20how%20we%20pay%20tipped%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20too%2C%20through%20a%20new%20policy%20that%20could%20ensure%20them%20a%20more%20consistent%20income.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHonestly%2C%20I%20think%20that's%20how%20it%20should%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERight%20now%2C%20tipped%20workers%20in%20Chicago%20receive%20what's%20called%20a%20subminimum%20wage%20of%20%249%20to%20%249.48%20depending%20on%20how%20many%20employees%20there%20are%20at%20the%20establishment.%20If%20a%20tipped%20worker's%20wages%20plus%20tips%20do%20not%20equal%20at%20least%20the%20full%20minimum%20wage%20%E2%80%94%20%2415%20for%20an%20employer%20with%204%20to%2020%20workers%2C%20and%20%2415.80%20for%20those%20with%20more%20than%2021%20workers%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chicago.gov%2Fcity%2Fen%2Fdepts%2Fbacp%2Fsupp_info%2Fminimumwageinformation.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eaccording%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20to%20the%20City%20of%20Chicago%20%E2%80%94%20the%20employer%20must%20make%20up%20the%20difference.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20July%2C%20the%20city%20introduced%20a%20new%20ordinance%20that%20will%20guarantee%20these%20workers%20a%20%2415.80%20minimum%20wage%20plus%20any%20tips%20they%20receive%20on%20top%20of%20that%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblockclubchicago.org%2F2023%2F07%2F19%2Fmayor-alderpeople-introduce-ordinance-to-end-subminimum-wage-for-tipped-workers-in-chicago%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DChicago%2527s%2520minimum%2520wage%2520for%2520most%2Con%252Dthe%252Djob%2520tips.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eaccording%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20to%20Block%20Club%20Chicago.%20If%20the%20ordinance%20passes%20through%20the%20city%20council%20businesses%20will%20be%20required%20to%20meet%20the%20new%20wage%20guidelines%20by%20July%202025%2C%20Block%20Club%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frestaurant-no-tipping-thattu-chicago-prices-higher-worthwhile-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693819701000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ed239f3c42320019c06619%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frestaurant-no-tipping-thattu-chicago-prices-higher-worthwhile-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Vinod%20Kalathil%20and%20his%20wife%20adopted%20a%20no-tip%20policy%20at%20Thattu%20in%20Chicago%20after%20realizing%20diners%20didn't%20like%20leaving%20tips%20using%20credit%20card%20readers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lvaranasi%40insider.com%20(Lakshmi%20Varanasi)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A34%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frestaurant-no-tipping-thattu-chicago-prices-higher-worthwhile-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ex%20lovers%20Kartik-Sara%20pose%20for%20a%20selfie%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693819699000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103353703%2Cimgsize-221008.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fex-lovers-kartik-aaryan-and-sara-ali-khan-pose-together-for-a-selfie-kriti-sanon-joins-them-see-inside%2Farticleshow%2F103353815.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103353815.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EKartik%20Aaryan%20and%20Sara%20Ali%20Khan%20were%20once%20known%20to%20be%20going%20steady.%20However%2C%20for%20reasons%20best%20known%20to%20them%2C%20the%20duo%20split%20up%20around%20three%20years%20back.%20However%2C%20it%20seems%20like%20there%20is%20no%20bitterness%20between%20the%20two%2C%20as%20the%20duo%20recently%20posed%20for%20a%20pic%20at%20the%20success%20party%20of%20Gadar%202%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fex-lovers-kartik-aaryan-and-sara-ali-khan-pose-together-for-a-selfie-kriti-sanon-joins-them-see-inside%2Farticleshow%2F103353815.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20happens%20to%20sharks%2C%20dolphins%2C%20alligators%2C%20and%20other%20marine%20life%20during%20a%20hurricane%3F%20Experts%20explain%20why%20the%20storm's%20aftermath%20is%20often%20more%20deadly%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20blacktip%20shark%20swims%20near%20a%20school%20of%20fish%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20near%20South%20Africa%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f230a11e6afd00196a5eb3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EResearchers%20studied%20how%20blacktip%20sharks%20travel%20when%20tropical%20storms%20and%20hurricanes%20approach.%3Cp%3EReinhard%20Dirscherl%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHurricanes%20affect%20marine%20life%20differently%2C%20depending%20on%20whether%20they%20can%20move%20or%20are%20stationary.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EMarine%20mammals%20and%20fish%20often%20head%20for%20deeper%20water%2C%20but%20seagrass%20and%20oysters%20have%20to%20stay%20put.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAfter%20a%20hurricane%2C%20increased%20levels%20of%20freshwater%2C%20bacteria%2C%20and%20debris%20can%20also%20harm%20marine%20life.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20strong%20hurricanes%20hit%20land%2C%20the%20uprooted%20trees%2C%20destroyed%20homes%2C%20and%20other%20devastation%20are%20highly%20visible.%20What%20happens%20in%20the%20marine%20environments%20where%20they%20churn%20water%20and%20disrupt%20sediment%20isn't%20always%20as%20obvious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20vast%20array%20of%20marine%20life%20lives%20along%20the%20Florida%20peninsula%2C%20the%20US%20state%20where%20hurricanes%20make%20landfall%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aoml.noaa.gov%2Fhrd-faq%2F%23landfalls-by-state%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20often%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Florida%20Keys%20have%20coral%20reefs.%20Near%20the%20panhandle%2C%20there%20are%20temperate%20marshes%20and%20seagrass%20meadows.%20And%20the%20plants%20and%20animals%20in%20these%20various%20regions%20respond%20differently%20to%20hurricanes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20not%20all%20hurricanes%20have%20the%20same%20effects%2C%20said%20Melissa%20May%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20marine%20biology%20at%20Florida%20Gulf%20Coast%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20storm%20surge%20can%20act%20like%20an%20unusually%20high%20tide%20and%20leave%20some%20marine%20environments%20relatively%20undisturbed%20during%20the%20hurricane%20itself%2C%20she%20said.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20storm's%20aftermath%20can%20have%20its%20own%20devastating%20effects%2C%20from%20changes%20in%20salinity%20to%20an%20influx%20of%20sediment%20and%20bacteria.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20happens%20to%20marine%20life%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0d%3C%2Fstrong%3Euring%20a%20hurricane%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20typical%20year%2C%20about%2010%20hurricanes%20will%20develop%20in%20the%20Atlantic%20basin%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean%2C%20Gulf%20of%20Mexico%2C%20and%20Caribbean%20Sea%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nhc.noaa.gov%2Fclimo%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20force%20of%20a%20hurricane%20can%20create%2060-foot%20waves%20that%20churn%20together%20cold%20water%20from%20the%20depths%20with%20the%20warmer%20surface%20water.%20Its%20currents%20can%20stir%20up%20sediment%20as%20deep%20as%20300%20feet%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foceanservice.noaa.gov%2Ffacts%2Fhurricanes-sea-life.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20NOAA%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20marine%20mammals%20and%20fish%20can%20move%20to%20deeper%2C%20calmer%20waters.%20Researchers%20followed%20the%20movements%20of%20blacktip%20sharks%20during%20a%202001%20tropical%20storm%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1046%2Fj.1095-8649.2003.00250.x%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20left%20the%20area%20before%20it%20made%20landfall%20and%20returned%20after%20five%20to%2013%20days.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20hypothesized%20that%20lower%20barometric%20pressure%2C%20temperature%20changes%20in%20the%20water%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fisheries.noaa.gov%2Ffeature-story%2Fare-fish-impacted-hurricanes%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esimilar%20cues%3C%2Fa%3E%20alert%20fish%20that%20a%20storm%20is%20imminent.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3D6262adeddd13a8b47bae6eb31f07ea29c43810ca3f5b8650fb80b7dfaf55e0b6%26postID%3D64f22b2afe7de7351163b241%26postSlug%3Dhurricane-effects-environment-marine-mammals-fish-plants-2023-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41598-018-37527-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2019%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20increased%20waves%20at%20the%20surface%20stirring%20water%20at%20the%20seafloor%20prompted%20gray%20triggerfish%20to%20move%20to%20deeper%20water%20before%20hurricanes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20dolphins%20and%20other%20marine%20mammals%20don't%20manage%20to%20escape%20the%20path%20of%20the%20hurricane%2C%20they%20can%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fisheries.noaa.gov%2Fmarine-life-distress%2Fdisplaced-dolphins-post-hurricane-response%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecome%20trapped%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20ponds%2C%20levees%2C%20and%20other%20freshwater%20habitats%20where%20they%20can't%20survive.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222619%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Several%20people%20hold%20a%20dolphin%20stranded%20in%20a%20ditch%20after%20Hurricane%20Rita%20in%20Louisiana%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f22cb21e6afd00196a5880%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHurricane%20Rita%20stranded%20a%20dolphin%20in%20a%20ditch%20in%20Louisiana.%3Cp%3EReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHurricanes%20can%20be%20deadly%20for%20fish%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%201992's%20Hurricane%20Andrew%2C%20an%20estimated%209.4%20million%20saltwater%20fish%20died%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwater.usgs.gov%2Fnwsum%2FWSP2425%2Fandrew.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Geological%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20found.%20Sediment%20may%20have%20clogged%20their%20gills%20or%20the%20pressure%20changes%20may%20have%20formed%20deadly%20nitrogen%20gas%20bubbles%20in%20their%20blood.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20storm%20swirled%20sediment%20in%20freshwater%20environments%20and%20turned%20the%20water%20anoxic%2C%20meaning%20oxygen-deficient.%20An%20estimated%20187%20million%20fish%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weather.gov%2Flix%2Fandrewanniversary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edied%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%20Louisiana.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHurricanes%20also%20impact%20stationary%20or%20slow-moving%20marine%20life.%20After%20hurricanes%2C%20%26quot%3Bseagrass%20beds%20and%20oyster%20reefs%20have%20been%20buried%20by%20shifting%20sediment%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Valerie%20Paul%2C%20head%20scientist%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnaturalhistory.si.edu%2Fresearch%2Fsmithsonian-marine-station%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESmithsonian%20Marine%20Station%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20an%20email%20to%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20lots%20of%20storm%20surge%20and%20wave%20action%2C%20that%20can%20physically%20uproot%20the%20seagrass%2C%26quot%3B%20May%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHurricane%20Ian%20swept%20almost%20250%20baby%20sea%20turtles%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.floridatoday.com%2Fstory%2Fweather%2Fhurricanes%2F2022%2F10%2F06%2Fhurricane-ian-baby-sea-turtles-florida-shore-brevard-zoo%2F8176761001%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20shore%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20Brevard%20Zoo's%20Sea%20Turtle%20Healing%20Center%20housed%20them%20until%20they%20could%20be%20re-released.%C2%A0%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20corals%20rely%20on%20waves%20to%20break%20them%20up%20and%20distribute%20them%20to%20new%20parts%20of%20the%20ocean.%20Hurricanes%20can%20also%20bring%20in%20cooler%20water%20and%20help%20offset%20some%20of%20the%20effects%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-barrier-reef-death-coral-bleaching-climate-change-2018-5%5C%22%3Ecoral%20bleaching%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20when%20too-warm%20water%20causes%20corals%20to%20purge%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foceanservice.noaa.gov%2Feducation%2Ftutorial_corals%2Fcoral02_zooxanthellae.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esymbiotic%20algae%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20provide%20oxygen%20and%20waste%20removal.%20But%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livescience.com%2F60354-how-hurricanes-impact-underwater-marine-life.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverly%20strong%3C%2Fa%3E%20waves%20can%20break%20up%20and%20kill%20corals%2C%20too.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20happens%20to%20the%20ocean%20after%20a%20hurricane%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20powerful%20storm%20subsides%2C%20litter%20and%20waste%20can%20remain%20in%20bodies%20of%20water%20for%20months%20or%20even%20longer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20debris%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflorida-hurricane-ian-climate-change-adaptation-flooding-sea-level-rise-2022-10%5C%22%3EHurricane%20Ian%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20our%20estuaries%2C%26quot%3B%20May%20said.%20Dozens%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnbc-2.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F03%2F08%2Fvehicles-still-waiting-to-be-towed-from-fort-myers-beach-after-hurricane-ian%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecars%20and%20boats%3C%2Fa%3E%20leaked%20gasoline%20and%20other%20chemicals%20into%20Estero%20Bay.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESewage%20can%20also%20make%20its%20way%20into%20waterways%2C%20bringing%20with%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fdo-beards-carry-germs%5C%22%3Ebacteria%20like%20enterococcus%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20E.%20coli%2C%20May%20said.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERain%20and%20flooding%20from%20hurricanes%20also%20bring%20an%20influx%20of%20freshwater%20to%20marine%20environments.%20%26quot%3BThis%20can%20be%20stressful%20to%20any%20organisms%20that%20don't%20handle%20large%20changes%20in%20salinity%2C%26quot%3B%20Paul%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarine%20life%20can%20often%20tolerate%20some%20changes%20in%20salt%20concentrations%20but%20not%20drastic%20or%20long-term%20alterations.%20For%20example%2C%20alligators%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhurricane-ian-knocks-out-entire-section-florida-sanibel-causeway-2022-9%5C%22%3ESanibel%20Island%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20Hurricane%20Ian%20hit%20hard%2C%20were%20affected%20by%20the%20saltier%20ocean%20water%20the%20storm%20brought%20on%20land.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20alligators%20can%20tolerate%20salt%20water%20for%20a%20time%2C%20they%20cannot%20live%20in%20it%20indefinitely%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsccf.org%2Fblog%2F2022%2F10%2F21%2Fhurricane-ians-impact-on-keystone-species%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESanibel-Captiva%20Conservation%20Foundation%3C%2Fa%3E's%20Chris%20Lechowicz.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20marine%20dolphins%20can%20only%20live%20in%20freshwater%20for%20a%20short%20time%20without%20suffering%20serious%20effects.%20Overexposure%20to%20freshwater%20after%20Hurricane%20Katrina%20may%20have%20caused%20a%20deadly%20skin%20disease%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fsmart-news%2Fclimate-change-fueling-fatal-disease-outbreak-dolphins-180976663%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebottlenose%20dolphins%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreshwater%20has%20other%20effects%2C%20too.%20%26quot%3BRivers%20tend%20to%20have%20a%20lot%20more%20sediment%20than%20ocean%20water%2C%20and%20they%20tend%20to%20have%20a%20lot%20higher%20concentrations%20of%20nutrients%20from%20coastal%20runoff%2C%26quot%3B%20May%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20hurricane%20pushes%20river%20water%20into%20the%20marine%20system%2C%20it%20creates%20favorable%20conditions%20for%20the%20formation%20of%20large%20algae%20blooms.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20manatee%20eats%20seagrass%20at%20Ellie%20Schiller%20Homosassa%20Springs%20Wildlife%20State%20Park%2C%20in%20Homosassa%2C%20Florida%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f22f671b7ced0019c6f020%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAfter%20Hurricane%20Ian%2C%20manatees%20around%20Florida%20starved%20as%20it%20became%20difficult%20to%20find%20seagrass%2C%20their%20main%20food%20source.%3Cp%3EMarco%20Bello%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20these%20cascading%20effects%20from%20the%20hurricane%2C%26quot%3B%20May%20said.%20For%20example%2C%20algal%20blooms%20after%20Hurricane%20Ian%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thetimes.co.uk%2Farticle%2Fwhat-happened-to-floridas-manatees-after-hurricane-ian-jwrn9lscr%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edidn't%20allow%3C%2Fa%3E%20sunlight%20to%20reach%20the%20seagrass%2C%20a%20primary%20food%20source%20for%20manatees.%20This%20put%20stress%20on%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.miami.edu%2Fstories%2F2022%2F02%2Fno-longer-endangered%2C-manatees-now-face-another-crisis.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealready%20threatened%3C%2Fa%3E%20population%20of%20sea%20cows%20in%20Florida.%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHurricanes%20are%20natural%20events%2C%20May%20pointed%20out.%20%26quot%3BOur%20ecosystems%20are%20actually%20designed%20every%20once%20in%20a%20while%20to%20kind%20of%20get%20wiped%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20But%20they%20also%20need%20sufficient%20time%20to%20recover%20before%20the%20next%20one%20comes%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClimate%20change%20may%20not%20increase%20the%20number%20of%20hurricanes%2C%20but%20it%20could%20make%20them%20more%20intense%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimate.nasa.gov%2Fnews%2F3184%2Fa-force-of-nature-hurricanes-in-a-changing-climate%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20NASA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20higher%20storm%20surges%20and%20more%20flooding%2C%20both%20of%20which%20are%20bad%20news%20for%20ocean%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhurricane-effects-environment-marine-mammals-fish-plants-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%2