ow%2F103348110.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Manipur%3A%20Criminalising%20Journalism%20Again%2C%20Police%20Files%20FIR%20Against%20Editors%20Guild%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01002307%2FManipur-bunker-II.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Manipur%20police%20has%20filed%20an%20FIR%20against%20the%20fact-finding%20team%20from%20the%20Editors%E2%80%99%20Guild%20of%20India%20(EGI)%20that%20had%20visited%20Manipur%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feditorsguild.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FEGI-report-on-Manipur.pdf%5C%22%3Epublished%20a%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20media%20coverage%20of%20the%20ethnic%20conflict.%20The%20FIR%20invokes%20Section%2066A%20of%20the%20Information%20Technology%20(IT)%20Act%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20struck%20down%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20times%20since%20then%2C%20the%20court%20has%20told%20the%20police%20across%20states%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fno-citizen-can-be-prosecuted-under-scrapped-section-66a-of-it-act-sc%5C%22%3Estop%20charging%20people%20under%20this%20section%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20the%20police%20are%20yet%20to%20pay%20heed%20to%20this.%20Under%20the%20annulled%20section%2C%20a%20person%20posting%20%E2%80%9Coffensive%E2%80%9D%20content%20online%20could%20be%20imprisoned%20for%20up%20to%20three%20years%20and%20also%20fined.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20this%20now%20non-existent%20section%2C%20the%20police%20has%20invoked%20sections%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20relating%20to%20promoting%20enmity%20between%20groups%2C%20injuring%20or%20defiling%20a%20place%20of%20worship%2C%20uttering%20words%20with%20deliberate%20intent%20to%20hurt%20religious%20feelings%20and%20statements%20conducing%20to%20public%20mischief%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscroll.in%2Flatest%2F1055363%2Ffir-in-manipur-against-editors-guild-for-report-on-media-coverage-of-conflict%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EScroll%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Section%2013%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act%20(criminal%20misconduct%20by%20a%20public%20servant)%20was%20also%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20state%20government%20has%20filed%20an%20FIR%20against%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Editors%E2%80%99%20Guild%20for%20trying%20to%20create%20more%20clashes%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Manipur%2C%E2%80%9D%20chief%20minister%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fani%2Fstatus%2F1698582733273088015%3Fs%3D46%26t%3DJ1VjQNDTFWrXclPML16-LA%5C%22%3EN.%20Biren%20Singh%20said%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20FIR%20names%20the%20authors%20of%20the%20report%20%E2%80%93%20Seema%20Guha%2C%20Bharat%20Bhushan%20and%20Sanjay%20Kapoor%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%2C%20Seema%20Mustafa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20FIR%20is%20based%20on%20the%20complaint%20filed%20by%20one%20Ngangom%20Sarat%2C%20a%20%E2%80%9Csocial%20worker%E2%80%9D%20who%20lives%20in%20Imphal%20West%2C%20and%20refers%20to%20one%20photo%20caption%20in%20the%20report.%20The%20caption%2C%20the%20complaint%20said%2C%20said%20that%20smoke%20was%20rising%20from%20a%20Kuki%20home%20%E2%80%93%20but%20it%20was%20in%20fact%20the%20home%20of%20a%20forest%20official.%20Based%20on%20this%2C%20the%20complainant%20decided%20that%20the%20report%20is%20false%20in%20entirety%20and%20%E2%80%9Csponsored%20by%20Kuki%20militants%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Editor%E2%80%99s%20Guild%20had%20recognised%20the%20error%20in%20caption%20and%20said%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20regret%20the%20error%20that%20crept%20in%20at%20the%20photo%20editing%20stage.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EThere%20was%20an%20error%20in%20a%20photo%20caption%20in%20the%20report%20released%20on%20Sep%202.%20The%20same%20is%20being%20rectified%20and%20updated%20report%20will%20be%20uploaded%20on%20the%20link%20shortly.%20We%20regret%20the%20error%20that%20crept%20in%20at%20the%20photo%20editing%20stage%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20(%40IndEditorsGuild)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FIndEditorsGuild%2Fstatus%2F1698287099265561025%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ESeptember%203%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Press%20Club%20of%20India%20has%20issued%20a%20statement%20against%20the%20FIR%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20strong%20arm%20tactic%20by%20the%20state%20government%20which%20amounts%20to%20intimidation%20of%20the%20apex%20media%20body%20of%20the%20country.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20a%20time%20when%20violence-marred%20Manipur%20needs%20utmost%20attention%20of%20the%20government%2C%20such%20a%20move%20by%20the%20state%20government%20would%20only%20make%20the%20matters%20worse%20and%20would%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20deliberate%20attempt%20to%20suppress%20the%3Cbr%3E%5Cntruth.%20It%20is%20a%20case%20of%20shooting%20the%20messenger%20rather%20than%20taking%20measures%20to%20restore%20peace%20in%20the%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20statement%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Editor%E2%80%99s%20Guild%20report%20had%20said%20that%20several%20reports%20on%20conflict%20coming%20out%20of%20Manipur%20were%20%E2%80%9Cone-sided%E2%80%9D.%20The%20media%20based%20out%20of%20Imphal%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20had%20%E2%80%9Ctransformed%20into%20Meitei%20media%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDuring%20the%20ethnic%20violence%2C%20journalists%20of%20Manipur%20wrote%20one-sided%20reports.%20In%20normal%20circumstances%2C%20they%20would%20be%3Cbr%3E%5Cncross-checked%20and%20monitored%20by%20their%20editors%20or%20Chiefs%20of%20Bureaus%20from%20the%20local%20administration%2C%20police%20and%20securi%3Cbr%3E%5Cnty%20forces.%20However%2C%20this%20was%20not%20possible%20during%20the%20conflict%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20noted.%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6Thee%20Meitei%20media%2C%20for%20that%20is%20what%3Cbr%3E%5CnManipur%20media%20seemed%20to%20have%20become%20during%20the%20conflict%2C%20acted%20collectively%20with%20editors%20consulting%20each%20other%20and%20agreeing%20on%20a%20common%20narrative%20e.g.%2C%20agreeing%20on%20common%20language%20to%20report%20an%20incident%2C%20refer%20ring%20to%20certain%20use%20of%20language%20or%20even%20not%20reporting%20an%20event.%20This%20the%20EGI%20team%20was%20told%20was%20because%20they%20did%20not%20want%20to%20inflame%20the%20already%20volatile%20situation%20further.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20EGI%20team%20also%20criticised%20the%20internet%20shutdown%2C%20saying%20it%20had%20made%20matters%20worse%20and%20%E2%80%9Calso%20affected%20the%20media%20because%20local%20news%20gathered%20without%20any%20communication%20links%20was%20not%20sufficient%20to%20give%20a%20balanced%20view%20of%20the%20situation%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20fact-finding%20team%20that%20has%20seen%20legal%20action%20after%20publishing%20a%20report%20on%20Manipur.%20In%20July%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-violence-fir-fact-finding-team%5C%22%3Ea%20case%20was%20registered%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20Annie%20Raja%2C%20Nisha%20Siddhu%20and%20Deeksha%20Dwivedi%2C%20who%20were%20part%20of%20the%20National%20Federation%20of%20Indian%20Women%E2%80%99s%20team%20in%20Manipur%20and%20had%20said%20in%20their%20report%20that%20Manipur%20was%20seeing%20%E2%80%9Cstate-sponsored%20violence%E2%80%9D.%20Before%20that%2C%20a%20leading%20academic%20and%20two%20Kuki%20activists%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhyderabad-university-professor-two-kuki-activists-summoned-by-imphal-court-for-interviews-to-the-wire%5C%22%3Esummoned%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20an%20Imphal%20court%20in%20cases%20filed%20by%20Meitei%20activists%20who%20claimed%20that%20statements%20made%20by%20them%20in%20interviews%20with%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0had%20%E2%80%9Cinflamed%20communal%20passions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693811266000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F01002307%2FManipur-bunker-II.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fmanipur-police-files-fir-against-editors-guild-fact-finding-team-cites-revoked-sec-66a%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BThe%20state%20government%20has%20filed%20an%20FIR%20against%20the%20members%20of%20the%20Editors'%20Guild%20for%20trying%20to%20create%20more%20clashes%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Manipur%2C%26quot%3B%20chief%20minister%20N.%20Biren%20Singh%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fmanipur-police-files-fir-against-editors-guild-fact-finding-team-cites-revoked-sec-66a%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Gadar%202'%20crosses%20Rs%20500%20cr%20mark%20in%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693811027000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103347838%2Cimgsize-79940.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fgadar-2-box-office-collection-day-24-sunny-deols-film-crosses-rs-500-cr-mark-in-india-well-on-its-way-to-beat-pathaan%2Farticleshow%2F103347838.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103347838.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E'Gadar%202'%20is%20set%20against%20the%20backdrop%20of%20the%201971%20Indo-Pak%20war.%20The%20film%20collected%20Rs%208.50%20crore%20nett%20in%20India%20on%20its%2024th%20day.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes